      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem">Portable Power Station vs Gas Generator for Job Sites — Which Is Right for Your Crew?</h1>
      <div style="color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem">June 17, 2026 · 11 min read</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>For decades, the job-site power equation was simple: you needed electricity where the grid didn't reach, so you bought a gas generator. Loud, smelly, thirsty — but it worked.</p>
      <p>Today, the equation is much more interesting. Portable power stations have matured from camping accessories into legitimate job-site tools capable of running saws, compressors, lights, and charging stations for an entire crew. The question is no longer "can a battery replace a generator?" but "when should you choose one over the other?"</p>
      <p>This guide breaks down every factor — noise, emissions, power output, runtime, cost, maintenance, and portability — to help you decide which power source belongs on your truck.</p>

      <h2>Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
